<item>
            <title>[LU-13380] CLIO: struct cl_io &quot;setattr&quot; attribute not getting copied to sub_io</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-13380</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This was see while working on &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-3606&quot; title=&quot;Implement fallocate() support for ldiskfs Lustre&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-3606&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-3606&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. For calls like falloc(), or any call which piggy backs behind SETTER interface and depends upon these attributes. It was noticed that the attributes was not explicitly copied to sub_io under lov_io_sub_init(). This was resulting in attributes under &quot;cl_io.ci_setattr&quot; coming out as 0 as it enters OSC layer. Resulting in osc_io_setattr_start() getting attributes as all 0.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="58467">LU-13380</key>
